{"key":"post-19451698","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>19451698</id>\n<content>Don't add spawn.&amp;nbsp; Leave it alone.&amp;nbsp; The mycelium will grow slowly at first, but then gains speed later.&amp;nbsp; If you mix it up now, you start over and it takes longer, even if you add more spawn.&amp;nbsp; I've used a 1:20 spawn rate with success, and regularly now use 1:10 simply to make my spawn go farther.&amp;nbsp; I'd say using 1:10 only results in a few extra days of colonization time over a 1:4 ratio.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You should always make sure all the grains are covered.&amp;nbsp; After mixing or layering spawn and substrate, always make sure there's at least a thin layer of substrate on top.&amp;nbsp; Don't leave grains exposed on the surface as it leads to much higher rates of contamination.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>19451931</next>\n<prev>19451659</prev>\n<first>19450775</first>\n<last>19453634</last>\n<when>1390314381</when>\n<utime>01/21/14 04:26 PM</utime>\n</post>"}